sec.p:
In the study of ref. 33, the authors reconstruct the original, full extent of LIPs when and where they were emplaced as a series of digital polygons. They then determined a statistical relationship using the present-day aerial extent of LIPs and age (i.e. time since emplacement) and found an exponential relationship between the data. Reference 33 calculated a LIP half-life of 29 Myr (Eqs. (1) and (2)), allowing us to calculate a fractional area of each LIP at a time after its emplacement (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
